  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>Romano pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large pieces </p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil </strong>and put in the oven for 20 min or until softened </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-1.2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-1.2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-1.2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-1.2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-1.2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>\n<p>Return the <strong>linguine</strong> to the pot<strong> </strong>and keep warm </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel the <strong>garlic</strong> </p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the baking tray, drizzle with<strong> olive oil</strong> and return the tray to the oven for 10-15 min or until softened </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-3.2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1388.-step-3.2-x400.jpg",
